Throughout Chinese history, the tiger has been seen as a very unique animal. Its power, its ferocity, its pride, and its beauty strike people as both awe-inspiring and charming. So many Chinese myths, poems, paintings and artifacts have tigers in them. To rediscover the symbolical of the tiger in traditional Chinese culture, CGTN anchor Wang Guan visits the National Museum of China and checks out some cool Chinese tiger-inspired artifacts from thousands of years ago.